<p>Cardano&#8217;s prospects for success are called into question when examining the reality behind its scalability and development milestones.</p>



<p>While Cardano aims to be a scalable blockchain platform, it faces challenges in achieving this goal. The project&#8217;s development milestones have been delayed numerous times, raising concerns about its ability to deliver on its promises. </p>



<p>Scalability is crucial for any blockchain platform to handle a large number of transactions efficiently, and Cardano&#8217;s progress in this area has been slow. Without addressing scalability issues, Cardano risks falling behind competing platforms that offer faster and more efficient transaction processing.</p>



<p>Furthermore, the repeated delays in achieving development milestones raise doubts about the project&#8217;s overall management and execution capabilities. To ensure its survival and potential revival, Cardano must prioritize and accelerate efforts to achieve scalability and meet its development milestones.</p>



