<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Tokenomics: Understanding ADA&#8217;s Supply and Demand</h3>



<p>An analysis of Cardano&#8217;s tokenomics reveals the potential investment opportunity presented by ADA&#8217;s supply and demand dynamics from an economic perspective. </p>



<p>Tokenomics refers to the economic principles that govern the supply, demand, and distribution of a cryptocurrency token. In the case of ADA, the supply is fixed at 45 billion tokens, with a circulating supply of around 31 billion. This limited supply creates scarcity, which can drive up demand and potentially increase the value of ADA. </p>



<p>Additionally, Cardano&#8217;s focus on scalability, interoperability, and sustainability has attracted a growing community of developers and users, further increasing demand for ADA. The table below provides a snapshot of ADA&#8217;s tokenomics:</p>



