<p>The emission schedule of ADA refers to the rate at which new tokens are created and added to the circulating supply. In Cardano, the emission schedule follows a predetermined plan that gradually releases new ADA tokens over time. This approach aims to ensure a fair and balanced distribution while maintaining a stable and sustainable monetary policy.</p>



<p>The monetary policy of ADA involves factors such as inflation, supply, and demand, which are carefully managed to maintain the overall value and stability of the token.</p>



